benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{childAccountId}/transferCredit - Move a given child credit to the parent level

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01 and @TC02 cover successful transfer with correct headers and data.
Non-Existing Resources: @TC04 and @TC05 cover cases where child or parent accounts do not exist.
Missing Required Header: @TC06 tests missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Malformed childAccountId: @TC07 covers invalid UUID format.
Extra Headers: @TC08 tests ignoring unsupported headers.
Security & Authorization: @TC10 and @TC11 cover unauthorized access and malicious payloads.
No Credit or Zero Credit: @TC03 covers insufficient credit scenario.
Not Found & Empty DB: @TC12 covers no accounts in database.
Concurrency & Performance: @TC14 and @TC13 address concurrent requests and performance with large datasets.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC16 and @TC17 cover double transfer prevention and backward compatibility.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or expired tokens or permission checks beyond @TC10.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Partial Input Formats: Limited testing of unexpected header formats or partial/malformed input data beyond @TC15.
Response Content: No detailed validation of response bodies for error messages or detailed audit logs beyond status codes.
Edge Cases: Missing tests for extremely large credit amounts or boundary conditions in credit values.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling when datasets are large.
Include explicit authorization tests with invalid or expired tokens.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under load.
Test for caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Expand input validation tests for headers with unexpected or partial formats.
Validate response bodies for detailed error messages and audit log entries.
Create tests for boundary conditions with very large or small credit values.
